`setDescriptors` is **outside the scope of the event handler** for it&#39;s only called when promise is resolved.

Thus, you would need to make use of a [state callback](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/42038590/when-to-use-react-setstate-callback) to properly manage descriptor versions.

```
.then((response) =&gt; {
  setDescriptors((descriptors) =&gt; ( // use state callback
    descriptors.map((desc) =&gt;
      desc.id === id ? { ...desc, ...response.data } : desc
    ) 
  })
}
