Your variables `min` and `max` are defined with **block** level scope. Move the declarations to before the `if` / `else`. Like,

    double max, min;
    if(input1 &gt; input) {
        max = input1;
        min = input;
    } else {
        max = input;
        min = input1;
    }

**or**

    double max = Math.max(input1, input);
    double min = Math.min(input1, input);

When you declare variables with a method or code block, they are limited in scope to that code block, so

    {
        double max = input1;
        double min = input ;
    }

means that `max` and `min` are limited in scope to this code block.

Declare them before this code block (same as `input` and `input1`).

And then you can use as

    double max = 0.00;
    double min = 0.00;
    if(input1 &gt; input) {
        max = input1;
        min = input ;
     }
     else {
         max = input ;
         min = input1;
    }

